   Bond Corp. Holdings is in talks to sell its 66% stake in
Bond Corp. International to Tompson Pacific Ltd. and a group
of unrelated parties, according to the Hong Kong Stock
Exchange.
   The announcement about the Australian company, the
flagship of Alan Bond's troubled corporate empire, comes
after speculation over the fate of the investment holding
subsidiary. BCIL has sold off nearly all of its assets in the
past 18 months, keeping only its 50% stake in a Rome property
development site and a brewery in China.
