<LP>
   CUPERTINO, Calif. -- Measurex Corp., citing a decline in
sales, said fiscal second-quarter earnings will be about 60%
lower than a year ago; the company said it is trimming
expenses to bolster earnings.
   The maker of computer-integrated manufacturing systems had
net income of $10.2 million, or 54 cents a share, on revenue
of $72 million, in the 1989 second quarter. The current
second quarter ends June 3.
</LP>
