   In trading yesterday on the New York Stock Exchange,
Measurex closed at $20.50, down $1.625.
   Measurex said last month that it expected results to be
down in the quarter, but in a statement yesterday, the
company indicated that the results would be "lower than
anticipated."
   The anticipated drop in revenue and earnings is due to
lower system sales and reduced gross margin percentages
related to lower volume and one-time costs for consolidating
certain operations, the company said. Even though
first-quarter European orders were at a record level, the
company said its delivery lead times were longer than
expected for many of its large, integrated measurement and
control systems.
